{"_id":"c0439657bb9803f3","name":"Improved Force Shield","type":"feat","img":"systems/foundryvtt-swse/assets/icons/force-technique.png","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you use the Force Shield Force Power, you can spend a Force Point to expand the radius of the Force Shield so that it protects you and all allies adjacent to you.","prerequisite":"Force Shield","special":"Alternatively, you can spend a Destiny Point to have the Force Shield protect a Vehicle you occupy, regardless of the Vehicle's size. If the Vehicle already has a Shield Rating, the SR of the Vehicle and the SR granted by this Force Power do not stack.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Legacy Era Campaign Guide","page":0,"tags":["force-technique"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"description":"<p>When you use the Force Shield Force Power, you can spend a Force Point to expand the radius of the Force Shield so that it protects you and all allies adjacent to you.</p><p><strong>Special:</strong> Alternatively, you can spend a Destiny Point to have the Force Shield protect a Vehicle you occupy, regardless of the Vehicle's size. If the Vehicle already has a Shield Rating, the SR of the Vehicle and the SR granted by this Force Power do not stack.</p><p><strong>Related Power:</strong> Force Shield</p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Shield</p>","relatedPower":"Force Shield"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"c11b3c4336c125d5","name":"Improved Force Storm","type":"feat","img":"systems/foundryvtt-swse/assets/icons/force-technique.png","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You can spend a Force Point when you activate Force Storm to fill the storm with Force Lightning. When you activate the Force Storm, and again whenever you spend a Standard Action to maintain the Force Power, compare the results of your Use the Force check to the Reflex Defense of one target within the Force Storm's area. If the Use the Force check result equals or exceeds the target's Reflex Defense, the target takes 3d6 points of Force damage.","prerequisite":"Force Storm","special":"You can spend a Destiny Point to increase the damage to 6d6 points of Force damage.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Jedi Academy Training Manual","page":0,"tags":["force-technique"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"description":"<p>You can spend a Force Point when you activate Force Storm to fill the storm with Force Lightning. When you activate the Force Storm, and again whenever you spend a Standard Action to maintain the Force Power, compare the results of your Use the Force check to the Reflex Defense of one target within the Force Storm's area. If the Use the Force check result equals or exceeds the target's Reflex Defense, the target takes 3d6 points of Force damage.</p><p><strong>Special:</strong> You can spend a Destiny Point to increase the damage to 6d6 points of Force damage.</p><p><strong>Related Power:</strong> Force Storm</p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Storm</p>","relatedPower":"Force Storm"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
