{"_id":"ccc959a2d0f81f3d","name":"Improved Force Lightning","type":"feat","img":"systems/foundryvtt-swse/assets/icons/force-technique.png","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"When you use the Force Lightning Force Power, you can choose to change the time it takes to activate to a Full-Round Action. If you do, your target must make a Strength check. If your Use the Force check result beats the target's Strength check, you push the target back 1 square plus 1 additional square for every 5 points by which you exceed the target's check result. If you push the target into a larger object, the target takes 1d6 points of damage.","prerequisite":"Force Lightning","special":"The target adds its Base Attack Bonus and size modifier to its Strength check: Colossal, +20; Gargantuan, +15; Huge, +10; Large, +5; Medium, +0; Small, -5; Tiny, -10; Diminutive, -15; Fine, -20. In addition, the target gets a +5 stability bonus if it has more than two legs or is otherwise exceptionally stable.","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Force Unleashed Campaign Guide","page":0,"tags":["force-technique"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"description":"<p>When you use the Force Lightning Force Power, you can choose to change the time it takes to activate to a Full-Round Action. If you do, your target must make a Strength check. If your Use the Force check result beats the target's Strength check, you push the target back 1 square plus 1 additional square for every 5 points by which you exceed the target's check result. If you push the target into a larger object, the target takes 1d6 points of damage.</p><p><strong>Special:</strong> The target adds its Base Attack Bonus and size modifier to its Strength check: Colossal, +20; Gargantuan, +15; Huge, +10; Large, +5; Medium, +0; Small, -5; Tiny, -10; Diminutive, -15; Fine, -20. In addition, the target gets a +5 stability bonus if it has more than two legs or is otherwise exceptionally stable.</p><p><strong>Related Power:</strong> Force Lightning</p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Force Lightning</p>","relatedPower":"Force Lightning"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"d36c0240ac48c171","name":"Language Absorption","type":"feat","img":"systems/foundryvtt-swse/assets/icons/force-technique.png","system":{"featType":"force","benefit":"You can use telepathy to forcibly learn a language from another creature. If the target is unwilling, you must succeed a Use the Force check against the target's Will Defense, as with the Telepathy aspect of the Use the Force Skill. You retain the ability to speak and understand this language for 24 hours.","prerequisite":"Telepathy","special":"","normalText":"","sourcebook":"Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide","page":0,"tags":["force-technique"],"bonus_feat_for":[],"uses":{"current":0,"max":0,"perDay":false},"description":"<p>You can use telepathy to forcibly learn a language from another creature. If the target is unwilling, you must succeed a Use the Force check against the target's Will Defense, as with the Telepathy aspect of the Use the Force Skill. You retain the ability to speak and understand this language for 24 hours.</p><p><strong>Related Power:</strong> Telepathy</p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Telepathy</p>","relatedPower":"Telepathy"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
